I'll announce Monday if I'm running for Congress.
On the other hand, Liviu Dragnea will announce next Monday if he will run for a leadership position at the next Congress.
I'll sing on Monday after the Executive Committee, if the date of the convention is set.
"I will announce if I will run for a position in the party leadership", Dragnea said at the end of Tuesday's session of the PSD's National Permanent Bureau.
Asked if the hesitation in announcing the candidacy was related to his file, Dragnea said he did not have this problem.
I don't have the issue you're referring to, but it seems fair and honest to all my colleagues in the party to announce whether or not I'm a candidate at the time that the date is formally established by Congress.
"It's the only motivation", said Dragnea.
The vast majority of the Social Democratic affiliates have proposed an extraordinary PSD Congress on October 11, and the exact date of the Congress will be decided on Monday by the party's Executive Committee.
The Career Fair offers thousands of jobs to 200 companies
200 companies are expected at the autumn edition of the Career Fair (TdC), an event that will take place in Brasov, Chisinau, Cluj-Napoca, Iasi, Sibiu and Tirgu-Mures.
The companies have several thousand job vacancies, internship and traineeships opportunities, and some of them are already announced on the official website www.targuldecariere.ro.
Recruitment, a growing priority for companies
According to statistics from the 100 Career Fair editions so far, most companies are interested, in addition to effective recruitment, in developing a strong employer brand among young people: 97% of their representatives said they would like to return to future editions, while 94% said they would recommend the TdC for recruitment and employer branding solutions.
There are also cases where companies choose to package hiring, precisely because that way they can think more organized recruitment.
The following will be on the list of those who will be present at the TdC in October and November 2015: Arvato Bertelsmann, Bombardier, Bosch, CIE Matricon, Competence Call Center, DB Schenker, Delphi, Office Depot, Preh, Renault, Schaeffler, Stefanini and Sykes.
Profile of the TdC candidate
The largest number of jobseekers in the TdC are students, over 59.70%, followed by university graduates - 23.05% and master's degree graduates: 10.38%.
The lowest rates are those who have completed their PhDs - 0.67 - and those who have completed high school or general school - 6.20%.
In terms of their areas of expertise, most of them work in IT and software, in the financial and banking sector, in insurance, marketing, advertising and media, or in the automotive and construction industries.
It is no news that the IT sector is on a continuous rise in the country.
As a result, a new edition of the IT Career Fair will take place this year, a niche event dedicated exclusively to enthusiasts and specialists in the field.
Among the business giants present at the 7th edition of the event were Accenture, Endava, KFC, McDonald's, msg systems, Siemens, Steelcase, Unicredit Business Integrated Solutions and Yardi Systems.
The Career Fair, 100 issues
Founded in Cluj in 2006, Career Fair is today the largest network of career events in Romania and the Republic of Moldova.
The autumn edition will take place in Chisinau (Army House, 2-3 October), Iasi (Palas, 6-7 October), Brasov (Army House, 14-15 October), Cluj Global (Polyvalent Hall, 20-21 October), Cluj IT (Polyvalent Hall, 22-23 October), Sibiu (Business Center, 28-29 October) and Targu-Mures (National Theatre, 5 November).
Details of the companies registered so far and the Career Fair can be found on www.targuldecariere.ro.
An Italian was caught at the Bors customs with immigrants hiding in TIR
Two Sri Lankan nationals were spotted Monday at Bors customs while trying to cross the border illegally, hiding in the trunk of a semi-truck driven by an Italian national.
Investigations revealed that the two were paying the driver 4,000 euros to be transported to France, the Border Police said.
At the specific check, border guards noticed a large travel bag in the cabin of the truck, containing personal belongings for several people, which is why they carried out a thorough check on the means of transport.
On that occasion, border guards discovered two men hiding in the trunk of the car, among the plastic boxes.
The verification results showed that the persons concerned, two men, aged 28, are Sri Lankan nationals and asylum seekers in Romania.
"In their investigations, the young people stated that they intended to reach France, and they contacted a conationalist, through whom they met the Italian driver, who offered to transport them to their destination, where they would receive 2,000 euros per person", the Border Police statement said.
The two migrants were given "criminal proceedings for the offence of attempting to cross the state border fraudulently".
Also, Pompeo B., a 45-year-old Italian national who was driving a Romanian-registered Renault Magnum truck carrying plastic boxes for an Italian company, was detained for 24 hours and was to be presented to the Bihor Court with a motion for pre-trial arrest.
How satisfied are Romanians in marriage: Men versus women
Most Romans are content with their relationships.
This is the conclusion of a study carried out on the occasion of the visit to Romania of John Gray, the famous author of the bestseller "Men are from Mars, Women are from Venus".
A total of 62% of respondents said they were 'very satisfied' and 'satisfied' with the overall quality of their relationship.
"Yet 18% report being 'slightly dissatisfied' and 'very dissatisfied' in their relationship, and another 18% report being 'appropriate'", the study concluded, as reported in a press release on Tuesday by Ziare.com.
The situation is slightly different when we look at the men's and women's responses separately.
So 28% of men are very satisfied, 39% satisfied, 17% satisfied, 6% very dissatisfied and 8% slightly dissatisfied.
For women, 33% were satisfied, 24% very satisfied, 8% very dissatisfied, 14% slightly dissatisfied and 19% chose the appropriate category.
When we look at the satisfaction level, we see that men are more satisfied.
As for the neutral state, we see a difference of two percent.
"Similarly, in the very unsatisfied situation, the biggest difference is recorded at the slightly unsatisfied response where we see a difference of 6 percent", the release continues.
The study also showed that a quarter of Romanians (26%) spend an hour or less together, 18% spend between five and eight hours together, and 45% spend between two and four hours together.
The authors of the study also report that "Romanians feel the need for a little more adventure in their lives (24%), followed by affection (21%), money (21%), security (20%), new (19%), sex (19%), respect 18%, trust 17%, pleasure 17%, connection 17%, knowledge 16%, protection 14%, importance 14%, learning 12%, freedom 11%, self-knowledge 10% and control 7%".
The study was conducted by Extreme Training from 1 June to 1 September on 1,369 people, with a calculated margin of error of 2.6%.
