German Vice Chancellor Sigmar Gabriel said on Tuesday that Europe was "ashamed" after Monday's failure of the Brussels ministerial meeting on the distribution of refugees within the European Union.
"Tonight (Monday night), Europe has once again been shamed", said Sigmar Gabriel, who is also the economy minister in Chancellor Angela Merkel's government, at a press conference.
Earlier, German Interior Minister Thomas de Maiziere suggested cutting EU structural funds for countries that reject refugee quotas.
European interior ministers, meeting in Brussels on an emergency basis on Monday, have failed to agree on the mandatory distribution of 120,000 refugees requested last week by the European Commission to deal with one of Europe's worst migration crises since 1945.
He was mayor for only half an hour
