Armor and water cannons at the border
Hungarian police have detached Humvee military vehicles equipped with machine guns at the border with Serbia after violent clashes on Wednesday, when water cannons and tear gas were used against migrants trying to break in from Serbia, despite Hungary having erected a barbed wire fence.
At least 20 police officers and two children were injured in the clashes, Russia Today reports.
So far 20 police officers have been injured and the ambulance service has picked up two children who were injured after being thrown over the security fence.
"We will rebuild the fence and we will strengthen it and we will protect the security of Hungary by any means", said Gyorgy Bakondi, the security adviser to the Hungarian prime minister.
Police tried to control the crowd with water cannons and tear gas, throwing plastic bottles, stones and pieces of pavement.
Authorities reported that several dozen migrants broke through the fence at the crossing between the towns of Roszke and Horgos and managed to enter the country.
Hungarian Foreign Minister Peter Szijjarto has called on Serbia to take action against "very aggressive" migrants at the common border.
There are reports that the Serbs have also increased their police forces at the border.
In the wake of Wednesday's incidents, Budapest suspended the crossing of the Roszke-Horgos border for 30 days.
Hungary is in concerted action to close its borders to prevent immigrants from entering.
If on Tuesday he announced that next to the barbed wire fence on the border with Serbia he will raise one on the border with Romania, towards the vehement protests of Bucharest, on Wednesday, the Hungarian Prime Minister announced the erection of a fence on the border with Croatia.
The rare disease a man suffers from
American Nick Hess was suspected by his family of being an alcoholic, his wife even filming him when he was dizzy, he could barely stand up, and his words were hard to understand.
Although the 35-year-old man said he had not consumed alcohol, he was clearly intoxicated.
When she first accused me of being drunk, when I wasn't, I thought she was crazy.
"But friends and family thought 'maybe he drinks alone, he's an alcoholic in secret,'" he says, according to the Mirror.
When he saw the footage of his wife with him, the Columbus, Ohio, man simply didn't recognize himself: "I looked into my eyes and I wasn't there".
'It was awful, I couldn't remember anything.'
Plus, his wife, who, though she doubted him for a while, eventually went with him to countless doctors, remembers Nick's breath smelling like alcohol.
The moment that put Nick on his mind the most was when, after a minor accident, when he was hit by another car, it was discovered that he had three times the legal limit of alcohol, although the night before he had only had one beer.
After years and countless investigations, it was discovered that Nick suffered from an extremely rare disease, "Auto-brewery syndrome".
Basically, his body is making all the carbohydrates he consumes ferment into alcohol.
The one who suspected it might be Nick's disease was the wife herself.
The disease doesn't have a cure yet, but since he stopped carbs, Nick hasn't had any of these episodes.
