The government approved on Wednesday the "National Immigration Strategy for 2015-2018" and the "Action Plan for the current year", documents considered to be "another stage that Romania is going through in the efforts to modernize the immigration management process on the national territory", according to a press release.
The source cited shows that the strategy aims at the efficient management of the phenomenon of immigration, including general strategic objectives, specific objectives and directions of action reflecting the policies established at European level, adapted to national realities.
In view of the problems faced by the States in the immediate neighbourhood of Romania, measures are envisaged for the united and coherent management of situations arising from the possible emergence of an influx of illegal immigrants into Romania, caused by crisis situations of a political, social, economic or military nature.
'The Romanian authorities will contribute to the creation of a flexible admission system, but at the same time will pay particular attention to citizens from states with potential migration or who may pose a threat to national security,' the source adds.
The strategy identifies a number of factors that may influence immigration and asylum, including the continuation of the conflict situation in Syria, the resumption of the conflict in Iraq, the continuation of an unstable situation in the areas bordering Romania (Ukraine, Transnistria), the perpetuation and intensification of the Israeli-Palestinian armed conflict.
The document also sets out a number of general strategic objectives related to immigration, such as: promoting legal migration, more stringent checks on the legality of the stay of third-country nationals in Romania and the appropriate application of removal and restrictive measures, and improving the national asylum system.
The national strategy shall also include specific objectives relevant to the transposition and implementation of the general strategic objectives.
These include: facilitating access to the Romanian territory for third-country nationals who meet the needs of the labour force, facilitating access for third-country nationals to Romanian higher education institutions for areas and professions identified as deficient.
The Commission notes that the 2015 Action Plan is a 'means to establish concrete activities leading to the creation of a flexible system to stop the growing migration phenomenon'.
Romania, in a European top on the labour market
Latvia, Romania and Bulgaria recorded the highest growth in total labour costs among EU Member States in the second quarter of the year compared to the same period in 2014, according to data published by the European Statistical Office (Eurostat) on Wednesday.
The index refers to the personnel expenditure of employers.
Thus, between April and June 2015, total labour costs increased by 1,9% in the European Union and by 1,6% in the euro area.
Romania, third in the EU in labour cost growth
The largest increases were reported in Latvia (7,9%), Romania (7,7%), Bulgaria (6,8%), Estonia (5,5%) and Lithuania (4,3%).
The only EU countries where hourly labour costs fell in the second quarter of this year were Greece (minus 2.9%), Cyprus (minus 1.2%) and Italy (minus 0.4%).
The increase in labour costs in Romania in the period April-June 2015 is mainly due to the increase in hourly labour costs in industry and services by 7,9% and 7,6%, respectively.
In the construction sector, Romania recorded an advance of 5.8% in hourly labour costs.
TVR management activity report rejected in committees: Stelian Tanase risks being fired
The culture committees of the Parliament rejected on Wednesday the activity report of the Board of Directors of the Romanian Television Society for 2014.
The report was rejected by 17 MPs, one against the rejection (Senator Varujan Vosganian) and one abstained.
The text of the report shall be forwarded to the Permanent Offices meeting.
They'll decide, probably next week.
The next plenary will be debated.
"I think given this situation it will be done relatively quickly", said the chair of the Senate Culture Committee, Georgica Severin.
He added that it was 'common sense' for the TVR management to be present at this meeting, since no representative of the TVR management was present at the meeting of the Culture Committees.
It was good sense to have the TVR leadership present because no one here has been subjected to personal attacks or anything like that.
The invitation was made to the CA members last night, about an hour before we knew what time it was, but today, after the meeting of the convened Bureau, I personally sent a fax to the TVR leadership inviting her.
I think the moment you're summoned, you're being budgeted, paid from public taxes and you're summoned to a meeting of the assembled committees even if you don't like living.
"Because it's your duty, you're in an institution subordinate to Parliament", Severin said after the meeting of the Parliament's Culture Committees.
He added that the financial aspects of the institution were discussed at the meeting on the basis of the negative opinion of the Budget Committees.
We've seen the debts continue, and the idea was that this year would be up to date, but they didn't pay off the historical ones.
